1
00:00:01,427 --> 00:00:04,449
1900年2月14日星期六

2
00:00:04,449 --> 00:00:07,452
一群来自阿普莉亚德学院的女学生

3
00:00:07,452 --> 00:00:12,456
在维多利亚州马其顿山 附近的海茵悬崖郊游

4
00:00:12,456 --> 00:00:14,458
整个下午

5
00:00:14,458 --> 00:00:17,749
好几名成员无缘无故失踪 

6
00:00:26,910 --> 00:00:35,381
{2c&Hd22#8FBC8F}{fn方正粗圆简体fs27}时间轴重调 风之子

7
00:01:12,321 --> 00:01:22,001
<font size=30 color=#98ff68>{\fn方正粗倩简体}
―― 悬崖下的野餐 ――

8
00:01:25,131 --> 00:01:28,130
我们所看到的
(girl's voice) What we see

9
00:01:28,130 --> 00:01:31,130
以及我们所似乎看到的
and what we seem

10
00:01:31,130 --> 00:01:35,119
都是一个梦 
are but a dream...

11
00:01:36,131 --> 00:01:38,120
梦中之梦
a dream within a dream.

12
00:02:07,132 --> 00:02:11,122
主演 雷切尔 ・ 罗伯兹

13
00:02:14,133 --> 00:02:18,123
主演 多米尼克 ・ 加德

14
00:02:20,134 --> 00:02:24,123
主演 海伦 ・ 莫斯

15
00:02:53,137 --> 00:02:58,421
根据约翰 ・ 林德西同名小说改编

16
00:02:59,746 --> 00:03:03,127
当夜色临近 来见我吧 爱人

17
00:03:05,109 --> 00:03:08,138
我爱你 名门的优雅

18
00:03:08,438 --> 00:03:11,139
还有你深邃的眼神

19
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:15,139
你甜美深远的表情

20
00:03:15,539 --> 00:03:18,139
还有你高贵的举止. 

21
00:03:19,186 --> 00:03:20,128
六

22
00:03:21,139 --> 00:03:23,129
七

23
00:03:24,461 --> 00:03:26,129
八

24
00:03:27,140 --> 00:03:29,140
九

25
00:03:29,850 --> 00:03:31,140
十

26
00:03:31,140 --> 00:03:33,130
十一

27
00:03:34,975 --> 00:03:38,141
我爱你 并非你美丽的头发

28
00:03:38,888 --> 00:03:42,130
如绒毛般柔软 如天空般光滑

29
00:03:43,142 --> 00:03:46,142
也不是因为你深深眼窝中

30
00:03:46,142 --> 00:03:49,142
丘比特的神箭

31
00:03:49,361 --> 00:03:52,142
你知道到底是什么原因吗 

32
00:03:52,882 --> 00:03:56,132
因为我爱你 一如你爱我一般 

33
00:04:35,146 --> 00:04:42,188
导演 彼得 ・ 威尔

34
00:05:00,020 --> 00:05:06,486
阿普莉亚德学院 1900年情人节

35
00:05:23,844 --> 00:05:27,150
萨拉 总有一天你一定会和我一起回家 

36
00:05:27,856 --> 00:05:29,151
去昆士兰

37
00:05:29,928 --> 00:05:33,140
亲自见见我可爱有趣的家人

38
00:05:34,151 --> 00:05:35,740
你愿意吗 

39
00:05:43,152 --> 00:05:47,152
萨拉 除此之外

40
00:05:48,004 --> 00:05:51,142
你还必须学会热爱其他人

41
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:55,542
我不会在这里呆很久

42
00:06:03,309 --> 00:06:04,548
你认为怎样 米兰达 

43
00:06:04,548 --> 00:06:07,154
有人鼓起勇气送给迈克劳小姐一张卡片

44
00:06:07,154 --> 00:06:10,744
写在满是小数点的座标纸上

45
00:06:15,154 --> 00:06:17,154
姑娘们 姑娘们 

46
00:06:17,593 --> 00:06:19,154
除非你们用更加优雅的

47
00:06:19,154 --> 00:06:22,155
能发出更小声音的方式下课

48
00:06:22,155 --> 00:06:23,655
否则阿普莉亚德太太

49
00:06:23,656 --> 00:06:26,155
今天就不会让你们去海茵悬崖郊游

50
00:06:26,155 --> 00:06:27,155
早上好 鲁姆莉小姐

51
00:06:27,155 --> 00:06:30,135
早上好 波蒂尔斯小姐

52
00:06:34,007 --> 00:06:35,731
我相信阿普莉亚德太太

53
00:06:35,732 --> 00:06:38,146
已经决定不让你去郊游 萨拉

54
00:06:39,703 --> 00:06:41,816
那意味着我们俩都不能去

55
00:06:43,493 --> 00:06:45,043
你可以走了 

56
00:06:46,719 --> 00:06:49,558
为圣瓦伦丁干杯 

57
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:25,150
法语 
Tais-toi, Irma. Miss McCraw vient d'arriver.

58
00:07:27,161 --> 00:07:29,161
她今天想学代数

59
00:07:29,161 --> 00:07:31,150
今天 

60
00:08:02,141 --> 00:08:03,164
早上好 姑娘们

61
00:08:03,164 --> 00:08:05,408
早上好 阿普莉亚德太太
[Together] Good morning, Mrs. Appleyard.

62
00:08:05,444 --> 00:08:07,130
年轻的女士们 天气对我们非常的照顾
Well, young ladies, we are indeed fortunate in the weather

63
00:08:07,130 --> 00:08:09,808
很适合我们 今天去海茵悬崖郊游
for our picnic to Hanging Rock.

64
00:08:10,008 --> 00:08:11,650
我已经通知老师了
I have instructed Mademoiselle

65
00:08:11,650 --> 00:08:12,950
如果今天暖和的话
that as the day is likely to be warm,

66
00:08:13,257 --> 00:08:17,705
穿过伍邓德的时候 你们可以脱掉手套
you may remove your gloves once the drag has passed through Woodend.

67
00:08:18,026 --> 00:08:22,065
你们要在岩石上 吃光带去郊游的食物
You will partake of luncheon at the picnic grounds near the rock.

68
00:08:22,065 --> 00:08:26,451
我再次提醒你们 那块岩石非常的危险
Once again let me remind you that the rock is extremely dangerous,

69
00:08:26,451 --> 00:08:30,866
因此 切不可顽皮地探险
and you are therefore forbidden any tomboy foolishness

70
00:08:30,951 --> 00:08:33,166
哪怕是在非常低的斜坡上
in the matter of exploration, even on the lower slopes.

71
00:08:33,166 --> 00:08:37,080
我还要提醒你们 附近的居民说那里有毒蛇
I also wish to remind you, the vicinity is renowned for its venomous snakes

72
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:40,168
以及不同种类的毒蚁
and poisonous ants of various species.

73
00:08:40,635 --> 00:08:43,168
总之 你们要在星期一写一篇
It is, however, a geological marvel

74
00:08:43,909 --> 00:08:47,080
有关地质方面的随笔
on which you will be required to write a brief essay on Monday morning.

75
00:08:48,035 --> 00:08:50,981
就说到这了祝你们玩的开心
That is all. Have a pleasant day,

76
00:08:50,981 --> 00:08:54,169
一定要留心自己的礼仪 要给学院树立风范
and try to behave yourselves in a manner to bring credit to the college.

77
00:08:54,819 --> 00:08:58,157
哈西先生 哈西先生 
Mr. Hussey! Mr. Hussey!

78
00:08:59,950 --> 00:09:02,169
我希望你 迈克劳小姐和老师
I shall expect you back, Miss McCraw and Mademoiselle,

79
00:09:02,169 --> 00:09:04,080
晚上8前回来参加烛光晚宴
at about 8:00 for a light supper.

80
00:09:04,130 --> 00:09:05,832
来吧 姑娘们
Come, girls.

81
00:09:08,169 --> 00:09:10,159
哇噢 
Whoa!

82
00:09:25,171 --> 00:09:28,860
阿普莉亚德女子教育学院

83
00:09:38,023 --> 00:09:40,441
这样对我们实在太好了
This we do for pleasure

84
00:09:40,441 --> 00:09:43,173
我们可以短暂地
so that we may shortly be at the mercy

85
00:09:43,173 --> 00:09:46,525
任由毒蛇和毒蚁处置
of venomous snakes and poisonous ants.

86
00:09:47,110 --> 00:09:50,062
人类到底有多笨 
How foolish can human creatures be?

87
00:10:45,178 --> 00:10:49,168
就在那 女士们海茵悬崖 
There she is, ladies. Hangin' Rock.

88
00:10:51,781 --> 00:10:54,179
穆罕默德来到了此山中
The mountain comes to Mohammed.

89
00:10:54,179 --> 00:10:57,252
哈西来到了悬崖上
A hanging rock comes to Mr. Hussey.

90
00:10:58,396 --> 00:11:00,780
她有500英尺高
More than 500 feet high she is.

91
00:11:00,870 --> 00:11:04,179
是火山岩 有数千年的历史
Volcanic, of course. Thousands of years old.

92
00:11:04,816 --> 00:11:08,119
哈西先生 她差不多有一百万年的历史
A million years old, Mr. Hussey, or thereabouts.

93
00:11:08,646 --> 00:11:11,694
是的 没错
Yes, well, that'd be right.

94
00:11:12,222 --> 00:11:14,180
数千年 数百万年
Thousands, millions.

95
00:11:15,153 --> 00:11:19,207
从某种意义上说 有种非常悠久的历史
Devil of a long time, anyway, in a manner of speakin'.

96
00:11:19,247 --> 00:11:21,745
才一百万年前
Only a million years ago. 

97
00:11:22,007 --> 00:11:24,404
实际上是最近一次火山爆发造成的
Quite a recent eruption, really.

98
00:11:25,181 --> 00:11:28,182
马其顿山周围的岩石
The rocks all around Mount Macedon itself

99
00:11:28,599 --> 00:11:32,171
一定有350万年的历史
must be all of 350 million years old.

100
00:11:34,672 --> 00:11:40,903
从上升处都是硅酸火山岩
Siliceous lava forced up from deep down below.

101
00:11:41,956 --> 00:11:44,128
那粗糙面的岩石
Soda trachytes

102
00:11:44,238 --> 00:11:48,409
在非常胶粘的状态下挤压
extruded in a highly viscous state,

103
00:11:48,409 --> 00:11:52,995
形成了我们现在所看到的 陡峭多棱的山脉
building the steep-sided mountains we see in Hanging Rock.

104
00:11:54,820 --> 00:11:57,709
坦白讲 她的历史非常年轻 
And quite young, geologically speaking. 

105
00:11:58,047 --> 00:11:59,856
才一百万年
Barely a million years.

106
00:12:00,935 --> 00:12:05,431
一百万年来就是为了等我们
Waiting a million years just for us.

107
00:12:34,567 --> 00:12:36,382
还要蛋糕吗 迈克尔 
More cake, Michael?

108
00:12:38,013 --> 00:12:39,921
不用了 谢谢 阿姨我
No, thank you, Aunt. I'm...

109
00:12:40,862 --> 00:12:43,257
我想四处走走
I think I'll just, um, stretch my legs a bit.

110
00:12:43,257 --> 00:12:47,004
哦 别走太远 小心点
Oh, don't go too far and be careful.

111
00:12:47,185 --> 00:12:49,221
可能有蛇
There could be snakes.

112
00:13:26,191 --> 00:13:27,395
你还好吗 
How's it goin'?

113
00:13:27,784 --> 00:13:28,908
还好
All right.

114
00:13:30,587 --> 00:13:32,277
他们吃完东西了吗 
They finished eating, have they?

115
00:13:34,196 --> 00:13:34,953
嗯 
Eh?

116
00:13:36,342 --> 00:13:38,603
上校和他太太 他们吃完东西了吗 
The colonel and the missus... they finished eating, have they?

117
00:13:38,662 --> 00:13:41,453
哦 是的 吃完了
Oh, yes, they have.

118
00:13:42,967 --> 00:13:44,765
我想马上就上去
Expect me up there in a minute, I suppose.

119
00:13:44,765 --> 00:13:46,183
收拾干净
Clear away.

120
00:13:52,595 --> 00:13:54,194
中午不可能
Can't be more'n midday.

121
00:13:54,194 --> 00:13:55,271
是的
No.

122
00:13:59,446 --> 00:14:01,790
我想我吃中饭早了点
I thought it was a little early for lunch myself.

123
00:14:02,774 --> 00:14:03,374
是的
Yes.

124
00:14:06,572 --> 00:14:07,875
要喝吗 
Drink?

125
00:14:08,560 --> 00:14:09,497
谢谢
Thank you.

126
00:14:15,196 --> 00:14:19,197
你知道 他们一直都 允许我推迟一个小时过去
You know, they always allow an hour longer than it takes to get 'ere,

127
00:14:19,197 --> 00:14:22,196
然后他们就直接离去
and then they got 'ere straight away.

128
00:14:23,661 --> 00:14:24,629
谢谢
Thanks.

129
00:14:32,051 --> 00:14:33,186
啊
Ah.

130
00:14:34,793 --> 00:14:37,197
倒不是他们没事可做
Not that they got anything else to do.

131
00:14:37,633 --> 00:14:40,534
我是说 他们从不毫无理由地出来散步
I mean, they never go for a walk or nothin'.

132
00:14:55,104 --> 00:14:56,189
快点 
(Mr. Hussey) Get on!

133
00:14:57,719 --> 00:14:59,190
快 
Come on!

134
00:15:13,130 --> 00:15:17,428
摘下帽子 我们现在就出发
Take your hats. Let's go walk about now.

135
00:15:40,431 --> 00:15:44,852
-为圣瓦伦丁干杯 
-为圣瓦伦丁干杯 

136
00:16:04,867 --> 00:16:07,444
我希望你已经学会了你的诗 萨拉
I hope you have learned your poetry, Sara.

137
00:16:08,528 --> 00:16:11,206
坐直了孩子 肩膀挺直
Sit up straight, child. Hold your shoulders back.

138
00:16:11,206 --> 00:16:12,718
你会驼背的
You're getting a dreadful stoop.

139
00:16:13,831 --> 00:16:16,207
那么 你诗歌背熟了吗 
Well, have you got your lines by heart?

140
00:16:17,634 --> 00:16:18,839
有吗 
Well, have you?

141
00:16:19,704 --> 00:16:22,207
我背不了 一点意义也没有
I can't. It doesn't make sense.

142
00:16:22,845 --> 00:16:25,560
意义 你这小傻瓜 
Sense! You little ignoramus!

143
00:16:26,195 --> 00:16:28,402
很显然你不了解 菲利西娅 ・ 海曼斯夫人
Evidently you don't know that Mrs. Felicia Heymans

144
00:16:28,402 --> 00:16:31,343
她是英国诗人中最为有名的一个
is considered one of the finest of our English poets.

145
00:16:33,207 --> 00:16:35,701
我背熟了诗歌的另外一部分
I know another piece of poetry by heart.

146
00:16:35,905 --> 00:16:39,713
它有很多诗节 比“金星号的毁灭”还多
It has ever so many verses, much more than "The Wreck of the Hesperus."

147
00:16:39,808 --> 00:16:40,587
不是吗 
Would that do?

148
00:16:40,814 --> 00:16:42,775
这首诗叫什么 
What is the name of this poem?

149
00:16:43,208 --> 00:16:45,010
圣瓦伦丁颂歌 
"An Ode to St. Valentine."

150
00:16:45,249 --> 00:16:47,810
我没听说过 你是在哪找到的 
I'm not acquainted with it. Where did you find it?

151
00:16:47,810 --> 00:16:50,210
不是找到的 是我写的
I didn't find it. I wrote it.

152
00:16:50,571 --> 00:16:52,199
你写的 
You wrote it?

153
00:16:54,564 --> 00:16:56,923
爱的存在 爱的包围 
"Love abounds, love surrounds..."

154
00:16:56,923 --> 00:16:58,211
哦不 萨拉 谢谢
Oh, no thank you, Sara.

155
00:16:58,211 --> 00:17:02,192
似乎有点奇怪 我还是更喜欢海曼斯夫人的诗
Strange as it may seem, I still prefer Mrs. Heymans.

156
00:17:02,714 --> 00:17:05,732
把你的书给我 能背多少就给我背多少
Give me your book and proceed to recite to me as far as you have gone.

157
00:17:06,966 --> 00:17:08,741
请把你的书给我 萨拉 
Your book, please, Sara.

158
00:17:10,953 --> 00:17:11,913
谢谢
Thank you.

159
00:17:13,211 --> 00:17:14,438
继续
Go on.

160
00:17:15,780 --> 00:17:17,201
我背不出来
I can't.

161
00:17:18,708 --> 00:17:20,083
一句也背不出来 
Not one line?

162
00:17:22,975 --> 00:17:24,794
我现在要离开你了 萨拉
I shall leave you now, Sara.

163
00:17:25,212 --> 00:17:27,471
我希望一小时内 我叫鲁姆莉小姐过来时
I expect you to be word perfect when I send Miss Lumley in

164
00:17:27,471 --> 00:17:29,563
你能背得滚瓜烂熟
in half an hour.

165
00:17:30,104 --> 00:17:32,043
否则 我会叫你上床睡觉
Otherwise, I'm afraid I shall have to send you to bed

166
00:17:32,589 --> 00:17:35,578
而不是让你站着 直到其他人郊游回来
instead of letting you stay up until the others return from the picnic.

167
00:17:49,215 --> 00:17:53,204
波蒂 波蒂 
[Whispering] Bertie! Bertie!

168
00:17:54,950 --> 00:17:56,957
天哪 你在哪 
Jesus, where are you?

169
00:17:59,216 --> 00:18:00,821
哦 米兰达 
Oh, Miranda!

170
00:18:09,216 --> 00:18:11,206
我喜欢这个
(girl) I like this one.

171
00:18:13,058 --> 00:18:16,080
我可以把你 比喻成夏季的节日 
"Shall I compare thee to a summer's day?

172
00:18:17,414 --> 00:18:21,535
你会更加的可爱更加的温和
Thou art more lovely and more temperate.

173
00:18:21,846 --> 00:18:25,006
大风摇动着五月的蓓蕾
Rough winds do shake the darling buds of May,

174
00:18:26,124 --> 00:18:29,206
夏季为所有人 出租了短暂的约会 …
And summer's lease hath all too short a date."

175
00:18:35,218 --> 00:18:36,278
真奇怪
(Mr. Hussey) That's funny!

176
00:18:38,218 --> 00:18:40,711
如果我的表没停止的话 我就砸掉它
Blowed if me watch hasn't stopped.

177
00:18:44,005 --> 00:18:46,036
12点正
Dead on 12:00.

178
00:18:50,197 --> 00:18:51,415
真奇怪
Real funny.

179
00:18:51,616 --> 00:18:53,221
法语 
[Speaking French]

180
00:18:53,221 --> 00:18:55,210
法语 
C'est tres jolie, n'est-ce pas?

181
00:18:58,221 --> 00:19:00,925
我想 小姐 你没有时间吧 
Uh, you wouldn't have the time, I suppose, miss?

182
00:19:04,222 --> 00:19:07,921
米兰达 你可爱的钻石表
Ah, Miranda, your pretty little diamond watch.

183
00:19:08,221 --> 00:19:10,221
不再戴它了
Don't wear it anymore.

184
00:19:10,894 --> 00:19:12,674
我的心脏受不了嘀哒声
Can't stand the ticking above my heart.

185
00:19:13,114 --> 00:19:14,211
啊
Ah.

186
00:19:15,222 --> 00:19:16,805
如果是我的话我 
If it were mine, I'd wear it always.

187
00:19:17,705 --> 00:19:21,544
我会永远戴着它 哪怕是洗澡的时候
Even in the bath.

